<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="would-rather-than">would rather ... (than)</h1>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.<strong>宁愿 / 宁可… (而不)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Will you join us in the game?
和我们一起玩游戏吧？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Thank you, but I’d rather not.
谢谢，不过我不想玩。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She would rather die than give in. 
她宁死不屈。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It’s getting late. I’d rather (that) you left now. 
天很晚了，你现在该走了。</p></div>

<p>注: would rather后的that从句要用虚拟语气。从句用“一般过去时”表示现在或将来的情况；用“过去完成时”表示过去的情况。  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Don’t come tomorrow. I’d rather you came next weekend. 
明天别来。我希望你下个周末来。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’d rather you hadn’t told my mother the truth. 
我真希望你没有把真相告诉我妈妈。</p></div></div>